# Penguin Rust — supercronic crontab
# Runs as rustserver (non-root). Logs to stdout (visible in kubectl logs).
#
# Static entries are baked here. start.sh appends dynamic entries (soft-wipe
# schedule) computed from WIPE_SCHED/WIPE_DAY/WIPE_TIME env vars at boot.

# ─── Plugin live-update checker ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Compare baked hashes against upstream releases every 5 minutes.
# Only acts when PLUGIN_SOURCE=github and an update exists.
*/5 * * * * /usr/local/bin/check-plugin-updates.sh
*/5 * * * * /usr/local/bin/user-sync.sh

# ─── Facepunch forced wipe ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# First Thursday of month, 19:00 London time. Warning sequence starts 60 min
# before. wipe-check.sh has a dom<=7 guard so non-first Thursdays are skipped.
#
# BST (Mar–Oct): 19:00 London = 18:00 UTC → warnings at 17:00 UTC
# GMT (Oct–Mar): 19:00 London = 19:00 UTC → warnings at 18:00 UTC
# Both entries are present; wrong-season fires and exits immediately (dom>7
# or stamp file already written by the correct-season entry minutes earlier).
0 17 * * 4 /usr/local/bin/wipe-check.sh
0 18 * * 4 /usr/local/bin/wipe-check.sh

# ─── Soft wipes (appended by start.sh at boot) ─────────────────────────────
# WIPE_SCHED=1w|2w|3w entries are added below this line dynamically.
